result.name: Blue Brick Bistro by Yoku Moku

reviews.text: We (3 of us) had lunch there 2 weeks ago (Monday). The overall experience was very good in terms of food and services. We ordered different dishes from the lunch menu so we could have a taste of different dishes. They don’t rush you to the next course which was good for a catch up. From entree to desserts, I cannot fault anything wrong. Cake roll is the signature dish. I like sponge cake and it’s what I like. I ordered the green tea flavour for extra $10. It worths it! Hopefully, I will be back again some time later!

A great Japanese style western restaurant which is also famous for its cake roll. For set lunch, the price is reasonable and the food is great. The most satisfactory experience is that even for set lunch, it was served extremely hot.

Fancy presentation and chillax environment. There are seats on the balcony where you can look out and down on Lee Tung Ave. Great for people watching.

The lunch set comes with soup and starter, main, and their Minami- Aoyama roll cake. 

Good food and good environment.
Kitchen and service really is excellent. Never enjoyed a "Free flow of oisters" before
A bit pricey, but food and service is good, especially the signature cake roll

Blue brick 
走進灣仔繁華的利東街，想不到找到一間非常有情調的西餐廳，甫進餐廳微黃的燈光，非常有情調，加上樓底很高，餐廳播着純音樂，整個氣氛也變得輕鬆，落地玻璃把窗外的景色映入眼簾，熙來攘往的人與這餐廳的氣氛形成強烈的對比。

來自法國及日本的生蠔是可以無限添加的，還包括了三種不同的醬汁，泰式辣汁， cocktail sauce，香蔥紅酒醋。
生蠔來自法國的Fine de Claire及日本兵庫縣， 法國的入口較有海水味， 而來自日本的較creamy。侍應細心地提醒我們由於來自法國的生蠔味道較濃郁， 故建議先吃日本生蠔，然後在吃法國生蠔。
個人覺得日本的生蠔賣相較為吸引，十分肥美，味道也是我喜歡的creamy。

烤美國西冷配意大利黑醋燒汁$388
Medium 
很喜歡吃西冷，肉質纖維夠厚，很有咬感，而且肉味濃郁。由於肉質較為厚，所以燒烤時間較長，特別適合肉味濃的客人呢。這個黑醋醬汁，也是很適合我們的口味，醋汁帶出肉類的鮮味，少許的酸味也令人胃口大開。

地中海式雜錦海鮮大燴$408
龍蝦湯底，see bass fillet，帶子、蟹腳、蜆、mussels， 附麵包。湯底十分濃郁，鮮味十足，也不會太鹹，份量以一個女孩子來說，也相當足夠。

但於晚是惠顧任何主菜，就可以以＄168任食時令法國及日本生蠔，仲可以半價優惠享用新款嘅雞尾酒，我哋點選左
Lychee gin martini $98
Gin tea mojito $98

特別一提，這裏的服務態度真的100分，每一位侍應都面帶笑容，可能由於星期日夜晚的灣仔，人流不算多，餐廳只有數枱的客人，除了適合大家把酒談歡，相對侍應也沒有平日的繁忙，每一次也笑面迎人，非常細心的為我們講解，令這一頓飯吃得更加愉快。

A great Japanese style western restaurant which is also famous for its cake roll. For set lunch, the price is reasonable and the food is great. The most satisfactory experience is that even for set lunch, it was served extremely hot.

Fancy presentation and chillax environment. There are seats on the balcony where you can look out and down on Lee Tung Ave. Great for people watching.

The lunch set comes with soup and starter, main, and their Minami- Aoyama roll cake. 

Good food and good environment.
Kitchen and service really is excellent. Never enjoyed a "Free flow of oisters" before

result.name: Lee Tung Avenue

reviews.text: A renovated walking street full of higher end shops and western restaurants.  Some decorations along the street for photo shooting.  Residential blocks were well managed.  Shops and food stores not so expensive were located in the same area.

One of the happening place in wanchai area, vibes of this place I always love. You can have places such as hotel, bars, icecream parlour where you can grab what you prefer then just sit and relax. There use to be events keep on happening at this place. One thing if you are a dog lover you will definitely see some fashioned dogs brought by their owners. I use to go at this quite often to get myself relax 😊
Nice walking mall. Very good atmosphere. Highly recommended !
A modern and beautiful avenue. Shops were beautiful. There is a new MTR entrance in the avenue with shops on both sides of the entrance corridor.

A colourful and recent addition to Wan Chai. Many restaurants at higher prices. A below ground supermarket for those with cash to burn. Great if there's an entertainer about, but otherwise keep moving through - there's more and better to be had in Wan Chai.
